[2026-07-04T02:05:00] TASK 1C — PIVOT
SPEC.md §15.7 says the OAuth handshake's automated tests should use
"`respx` stubbing `/oauth/request`, `/oauth/authorize`, `/oauth/access`."
In reality, `respx` only intercepts `httpx` traffic, and §8.1 pins
`requests-oauthlib` (built on the `requests` library, not `httpx`) as the
OAuth 1.0a client specifically because it's the natural/best-suited choice
for this dated OAuth version — so `respx` cannot see these calls at all;
this is an internal inconsistency in the spec's own tool choices, not a
case of external-API drift. Fix: added `responses` (MIT, free/open-source,
the `requests`-equivalent of `respx`) as a dev dependency and used it to
stub the three real Zotero OAuth URLs at the HTTP layer, preserving the
spirit of "stub the OAuth provider's endpoints over the wire" that §15.7
actually wants, rather than mocking at the Python-method level (which
would test less of the real request-signing/parsing path). Also
discovered `pyzotero`'s `create_items`/`create_collections` already
implement `Backoff`/`Retry-After` handling internally (`_check_backoff`/
`_set_backoff`/`error_handler` in `pyzotero._client`/`.errors`) — so
`zotero.py` does not need to reimplement §8.7's backoff pacing itself,
only translate pyzotero's per-item success/failure maps (and any raised
exception for a whole failed batch call) into CONTRACTS.md's per-PMID
`ZoteroPushResult` shape.

