`_neutralize_formula_injection` pinning the exact "prefix applied to
original value" contract. Verified these tests actually catch the bug
(not vacuous) by running the old raw-`startswith` logic standalone
against all three adversarial inputs first and confirming it left them
unneutralized, before confirming the new `_first_significant_char`-based
check fixes all three.
