Real architectural constraint not spelled out in BuildPlan.md: I own only
three middleware files, none of which are the Wave-1 route modules —
slowapi's usual `@limiter.limit(...)` per-route decorator would require
editing search.py/zotero.py/export.py, outside my ownership. Resolved by
using slowapi's `Limiter` class in its supported "middleware mode"
(`Limiter._check_request_limit(..., in_middleware=True)`), but driven
from my own plain-ASGI `InboundRateLimitMiddleware` with a small path/
method lookup table (`_RATE_LIMITED_ROUTES`) rather than slowapi's stock
`SlowAPIASGIMiddleware` (which only supports a single global
