[2026-07-05T17:02:31Z] TASK 5A — START
Starting BuildPlan.md Task 5A (Infra provisioning), SPEC.md §12.1-§12.3,
after reading Task 1A's log (db.py itself was Task 0.1's scaffold, only
touched incidentally by 1A for settings) and confirming db.py's
Turso-URL-string-only test coverage was explicitly noted as deferred to
this task. Orchestrator flagged a real, reproduced bug ahead of time:
sqlalchemy-libsql==0.2.0's `create_connect_args()` only lifts a fixed
allowlist of query params (uri/timeout/isolation_level/detect_types/
check_same_thread/cached_statements/secure) out of the URL into connect
kwargs — `authToken` embedded in the URL query string is silently
dropped, never reaching `libsql_experimental.connect()`, which needs
`auth_token` as an explicit kwarg. Confirmed independently by reading
both `sqlalchemy_libsql/libsql.py` (installed 0.2.0) and
`libsql_experimental.connect`'s real signature via `help()`:
`connect(database, isolation_level=..., check_same_thread=True,
uri=False, sync_url=None, sync_interval=None, auth_token='',
encryption_key=None, autocommit=...)` — no `secure` kwarg exists on the
real driver, confirming `secure=true` must stay a URL query param (it's
in the allowlist, popped internally by `create_connect_args` to choose
https/http scheme, never forwarded to `connect()`) while `auth_token`
must bypass the URL entirely and be injected via SQLAlchemy's
`connect_args=` on `create_engine()`, since I traced
`sqlalchemy/engine/create.py`'s `create_engine()` and confirmed it does
`cparams = dialect.create_connect_args(u)[1] | connect_args` — i.e.
user-supplied `connect_args` passed to `create_engine()` unconditionally
overlays whatever the dialect extracted from the URL, so a key like
`auth_token` that the dialect never recognizes still reaches
`libsql_experimental.connect()` correctly this way. Fixing
`backend/app/db.py` accordingly, then testing against the real Turso
credentials already present in `backend/.env` (not touching their
values), then generating `render.yaml`. Own: backend/app/db.py, a new
integration test file, render.yaml at repo root.

